                  <Text layoutX="52.0" layoutY="208.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Input and output (I/O) devices are essential parts of any computer system. They allow humans to communicate with the machine and vice versa. Input devices feed data and instructions into the computer, while output devices display or produce the result of computer processing. From typing on a keyboard to watching a video on a screen, every interaction you have with a computer happens through these devices." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
